[1] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Wed 11 Feb 2009
Source: Correio [Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://correio24horas.globo.com/noticias/noticia.asp?codigo=18520&mdl=50>


The Secretariat of Health of the State of Bahia (SESAB) confirmed
this Wednesday [11 Feb 2009] the death of the 4th child caused by
dengue this year [2008] in the state. The death of the 11-year-old
boy was confirmed today [11 Feb 2009]. He died in the early hours of
Sunday [8 Feb 2009] in the Luiz Eduardo Magalhaes Hospital, in Porto Seguro.

Besides the 4 deaths already confirmed, according to SESAB, another 6
suspected dengue deaths were reported since the beginning of January
[2009]. Of these, 5 are children of the municipalities of Jequie,
Porto Seguro and Itabuna. The other death is a woman of 27 years who
died in Jequie. [Samples from] all these cases are tested by the
Professor Goncalo Moniz (Lacen) Central Laboratory of Public Health.

Jequie municipality already recorded 2637 cases of [dengue] disease
(corresponding to 60 percent of total cases in the state).

According to SESAB, since the beginning of January [2009], 4272 cases
of classical dengue were registered throughout the state, and 84 were
in Salvador. As for the severe type of disease [DHF], 36 cases were
reported. The number of dengue cases in 2008 have grown 116 percent
in the whole state, according to SESAB.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

