[2] Brazil (Espiritu Santo)
Date: Wed 11 Feb 2009
Source: Abril [Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.abril.com.br/noticias/brasil/balanco-dengue-indica-inicio-epidemia-265216.shtml>


The 3212 cases of dengue reported last month in January [2009] in
Espirito Santo indicate the beginning of a [dengue] epidemic in the
state. According to the State Secretariat of Health, the number of
reported cases in January of this year [2009] is 400 percent higher
than that recorded in the same month of 2008, when there were 758
reported cases of the disease. Only last week [week of 1 Feb 2009],
the state had 1011 cases.

According to the Secretariat, the trend is that in a few weeks the
most explosive period of the disease will occur. The forecast is
based on the history of the last 2 years, where the peak incidence of
the disease began in March, after the rainy season. In December of
last year [2008], there were 1495 reported [dengue cases], up to 3212
suspected dengue cases in the past month [January 2009]. Last year
[2008], the peak occurred in the month March, when 3636 reported
[cases] were recorded.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT <promed@promedmail.org>

