[3] Bolivia
Date: Sat 14 Feb 2009
Source: AFP [edited]
<http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5jFtIghS_ounTWyWE6pXWd4B31rkA>


In the worst national [dengue] outbreak in a decade, 9 Bolivians have
died after contracting DHF, officials announced Saturday [14 Feb 2009].

The health ministry reported 64 confirmed cases of people with the
deadly DHF virus and some 15 800 people with regular dengue fever.
Local media reported the number of people affected by the classical
type of dengue fever was around 20 000.

Authorities have declared a health emergency in the central, eastern
and northern parts of the country, in the departments [state or
province equivalents] of Santa Cruz, Beni, Pando and Cochabamba.

The hemorrhagic variant of the dengue virus [infection] is much more
dangerous than the classic type because it causes violent internal
bleeding and swift fluid loss, which can lead to a quick, painful
death if not treated in time.

--
